title: For Sale:  Ballester Molina 1911 45 ACP Bianchi Very Cool
postcontent: This is a Gallester-Molina designed and built by the Argentine company Hispano Argentina Fábrica de Automotores SA (HAFDASA). The Ballester was originally called the Ballester-Rigaud (c. 1938–1940). The Ballester was designed to offer the Argentine police and military a less-expensive alternative to the Pistola Colt Modelo 1927, which was itself a licensed copy of the Colt M1911A1. Production of the Ballester-Molina began in 1938 and ceased in 1953. This example has a nice patina and was a police issued gun with a badge number of 239 on the slide. I didn't get the original grips but these Bianchi wrap around grips are some of the best I've seen. I have a set on my 1911. This uses any and all 1911 magazines and comes with one. If you like the 1911 but want one with a little history, this is the gun for you. Import marked.

title: For Sale:  COLT SUPER .38 AUTOMATIC
postcontent:
This pistol is the post-war "Fat Barrel" type with the outer barrel diameter the same as that of the .45. Further, it is a 3rd Model fat barrel with the rampant Colt logo on the left side of the slide.

This is a Colt "Super .38" that was manufactured back in 1951. As the model name would imply, this pistol is chambered for the .38 Super cartridge.

This cartridge was developed for the 1911 platform to produce higher velocity ballistics capable of penetrating automobile bodies, something the blunt .45 ACP had trouble doing. Sales were somewhat limited in the U.S. while the caliber became quite popular south of the border where military caliber handguns were prohibited.

The pistol comes with the original box which is numbered to the gun and includes the original instruction sheet, Overall condition is excellent, The original blue finish rates 97-98% overall with only light wear and handlijng marks. There is no rust or pitting. The grips are excellent, free of cracks or chips. The mechanics appear to be in perfect working order and the bores are excellent in both barrels

Winchester Model 94 Heritage Limited Editoin High Grade in .38-55 cal. 

This highly collectible model 94 is in a class of its own. It features a rifle configuration with deluxe fore-end cap, full magazine with half octagon, half round 26" barrel and cross bolt safety. It is engraved with 24k gold plated using the historic and elegant #3 Winchester engraving pattern. Winchester has a specail stock design with high grade walnut and a classic wrap around buttplate. The wood on this one is really outstanding, lots of stripes on both sides of the stock. A maximum of 1000 were to be produced but never Winchester never finished the run of 1000.

This Winchester was one of the last high grade Winchester products manufactured in New Haven, USA.

New in the box with all papers from Winchester.
